{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-generic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/b1-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-talk-about-past-experiences/task-15","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"assignments":[],"bilibiliIds":null,"block":"learn-how-to-talk-about-past-experiences","challengeType":19,"description":"","nodules":null,"explanation":"<section id=\"explanation\">\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Something</span> Koristi se u pozitivnoj rečenici da pokaže da nešto postoji ili se desilo. Na primer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">He found something unusual in the logs.</span> - Otkrio je da su uspomene bile drugačije od uobičajenog.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">She noticed something during the meeting.</span> - Nekaj nešto posebno ga je privuklo tokom sastanka.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Naprotiv, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">anything</span> koristi se u negativnim rečenicama ili pitanjima. Na primer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Hasi: <span class=\"highlighted-text\">He didn't find anything in the logs.</span> - Sećanja ga/je nisu pomogla da shvati problem.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Pitanje: <span class=\"highlighted-text\">Did she notice anything during the meeting?</span> - Pita da li je mogao nešto da vidi tokom sastanka.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>U negativnim rečenicama sa <span class=\"highlighted-text\">did not</span> ili <span class=\"highlighted-text\">didn't</span>, glavni glagol ostaje u svojoj osnovnoj formi (<span class=\"highlighted-text\">find</span>, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">notice</span> itd.), i <span class=\"highlighted-text\">anything</span> se koristi umesto <span class=\"highlighted-text\">something</span>.</p>\n<p>James kaže, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">That's when I noticed something odd</span>, što znači da je pronašao nešto tokom svog inspekcionog procesa.</p>\n</section>","helpCategory":"English","instructions":"<section id=\"instructions\">\n<p>Slušajte audio odgov